movie.title: Buckjumping
movie.description_intro: Buckjumping is a cinematic journey through the soul of New Orleans. The film explores different communities as they express themselves through movement, painting a dynamic portrait of a city's spirituality, defiance and resourcefulness.

movies.title: The Atomic Cafe
movies.summary: A compilation of 1960's films about what to do in case of a Nuclear attack and the effects of radiation, also footage of troop tests of the exposure to an atomic bomb.

movies.title: Space Dogs
movies.summary: Laika, a stray dog, was the first living being to be sent into space and thus to a certain death. According to a legend, she returned to Earth as a ghost and has roamed the streets of Moscow ever since. Following her trace, and filmed from a dog's perspective, SPACE DOGS accompanies the adventures of her descendants: two street dogs living in today's Moscow. Their story is one of intimate fellowship but also relentless brutality, and is interwoven with unseen archive material from the Soviet cosmic era. A magical tale of voyagers scouting for unknown spaces.

movies.title: The Dirty Dozen
movies.summary: They spend every waking moment training, playing, competing in the dirt. Take a look into the high octane lives of twelve professional off-road motorcycle riders in the most grueling, gnarly and incredible tracks and trails on the planet.
